It's these quiet, uneventful moments that capture our deep love, connection and mutual respect. The gallops through the woods are so liberating. The sweet high of soaring through a jump off is exhilarating. But these quiet moments. They're what I live for. And I wouldn't trade them for the world 🌎. I'm a lucky 🍀 girl to have found such a safe place for my heart ❤️ and such an amazing best friend. 
We don't have everything together. But together- we have it all. 
Love on your horses today and enjoy the small sweet moments because those are the ones that truly fill your soul 💕💕#horses #horsesofinstagram #quietmoments #darkhorse #bestfriend #liveinthemoment #love #connect

"The old ones say the Native America Women will lead the healing among the tribes. Inside them are the powers of Strength and Love given by the Moon and the Earth. When everyone else gives up, it is the women who sings the songs of Strength. She is the backbone of the people. So, to our women we say, sing your songs of Strength; Pray for your special Powers; Keep our people Strong." ➳ Village Wise Man, Lakota.

Ever since I was a child, as young as I could remember I would have vivid dreams of the being the Native America Tribes, the people, the land, the Connection to the Earth, the love and respect for her and appreciation for all she gives. It was always in me, it felt almost past over from a life before this one. I still have these dreams today, and the most powerful ones is when White Buffalo Calf Woman comes to me and shows visions of the future & helps me to connect. I think we as the human race truly have so much that we can learn from the ALL the indigenous people of this world especially when it comes to living in harmony with our collective Earth.
